get_synthetic_sin_data[source]

get_synthetic_sin_data(length=1000, n_sig=10, dims=2, per_ann_label=False, label_is_array=False, n_classes=5, has_multi_label=False, n_fold=None, split_pct=None)

Generates sample data with associated annotation positions at local maxima

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} 
Inputs:
    length:    Length of individual waveforms, expressed as int or tuple
               (min_len, max_len) 
    n_sig:     Number of timeseries waveforms to be generated.
    dims:      Number of dimensions in X array (2 or 3).  If 3, channel dimension
               will be added, 
    per_ann_label: Returns per-annotation labels
    label_is_array: Returns vector with of same length with non-zero values at
               annotation location
    n_classes: Controls number of unique classes 
    has_multi_label: Returns list of labels per row/annotation
    n_fold:    Optional number of folds, waveforms randomly distributed among folds 
    split_pct: Optional split fractions, expressed as int of train/valid or tuple
               (pct_valid, pct_tst) if train/valid/test

Returns:
    X:         Synthetic timeseries waveforms as np.ndarray if uniform, 
               L(np.ndarray) if ragged
    y:         Synthetic labels where label is index of row in X, returned as
               -- L(ann ...) where ann is per-row string
               -- L(L(ann ...)) where ann is per-ann string
               -- same format as X
    ann_pos:   List of annotated positions per waveform,  as L(L(), ...)
    splits:    Optional splits data if split_pct specified, as L(L(), ...)
    folds:     Optional folds data if n_fold specified, as L()
    *note: splits and folds are mutually exclusive```

Show signals with annotations - fixed signal length

{% raw %} 
X, y, anns = get_synthetic_sin_data(length=1000, n_sig=3)
print(f'X:{type(X)}   X[0,0]:{type(X[0,0])}  dtype:{X.dtype}')
print(f'y:{type(y)}   y[0]:{type(y[0])}')
print(f'X:{X.shape}  y:{len(y)}  anns:{len(anns)}')
for i, sig in enumerate(X):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 0.75))
    plt.title(f'{i}: label: {y[i]}  shape: {sig.shape}')
    plt.plot(np.arange(len(sig)), sig)
    plt.scatter(anns[i], sig[anns[i]], c='r', s=10)
    plt.xlim(0, len(sig))
    plt.show()

Show signals with annotations - per-annotation labels ('p', 'n')

{% raw %} 
X, y, anns = get_synthetic_sin_data(length=1000, n_sig=3, per_ann_label=True)
print(f'y:{type(y)}   y[0]:{type(y[0])}')
print(f'X:{X.shape}  y:{len(y)}  anns:{len(anns)}')
for i, sig in enumerate(X):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 0.75))
    plt.title(f'{i}: {sig.shape}')
    plt.plot(np.arange(len(sig)), sig)
    anns_p = [e for j, e in enumerate(anns[i]) if y[i][j] == 'p']
    plt.scatter(anns_p, sig[anns_p], c='r', s=10)
    anns_n = [e for j, e in enumerate(anns[i]) if y[i][j] == 'n']
    plt.scatter(anns_n, sig[anns_n], c='k', s=10)
    plt.xlim(0, len(sig))
    plt.show()

y:<class 'fastcore.foundation.L'>   y[0]:<class 'fastcore.foundation.L'>
X:(3, 1000)  y:3  anns:3
{% endraw %}

Show signal with labels formatted as vector. Non-zero values correspond to labels in above example

{% raw %} 
X, y, anns = get_synthetic_sin_data(length=(1000, 1110), n_sig=3, label_is_array=True)
print(f'y:{type(y)}   y[0]:{type(y[0])}  y[0][0]:{type(y[0][0])}')
test_eq([len(_a) for _a in anns], [len(np.where(_yy != 0)[0]) for _yy in y])

print(f'shapes - X:{len(X)} X[0]:{X[0].shape}  y:{len(y)}  anns:{len(anns)}')
for i, sig in enumerate(X):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 0.75))
    plt.title(f'X[{i}] - shape: {sig.shape}')
    plt.plot(np.arange(len(sig)), sig)
    plt.xlim(0, len(sig))
    plt.show()
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 0.5))
    plt.title(f'y[{i}] - shape: {y[i].shape}')
    plt.plot(np.arange(len(y[i])), y[i])
    plt.xlim(0, len(y[i]))
    plt.ylim(-1.5, 1.5)
    plt.show()
